{"author":"Iso Tester","data":{"alias":"unfed-liner-arson","description":"RISK 2 (over-cap growth). `src/rebar/_engine/rebar_reconciler/outbound_differ.py` grew +268 LOC to 1545 — now the largest file in the tree — and is allowlisted, so CI cannot stop the accretion. Split it along the EXISTING logical seam (the comment-diff cluster), not by line count.\n\n## Why\nThe prior audit's explicit watch-item materialized here. `compute_outbound_mutations` is also a 320-LOC body with 9 params incl. a mutable `absent_alive_fields` out-param.\n\n## What — careful split along the comment-diff seam\n- Extract the cohesive comment-diff cluster to a NEW sibling `src/rebar/_engine/rebar_reconciler/outbound_comments.py` (~250-300 LOC, clears the 100-LOC floor): `_diff_comments` (`:795-916`) + its satellites `_normalize_comment_body`, `_decorate_outbound_comment`, `_map_comments_for_create`, `_is_machine_marker_comment`, `_load_comment_limits`, `_load_adf` (per `docs/architecture.md:216`).\n- Keep field/label/link differs + `compute_outbound_mutations` (the orchestrator) in `outbound_differ.py`; it imports the comment module.\n- Fold in the smell fix: introduce an `OutboundDiffConfig` dataclass for the optional flags (`excluded_statuses`, `local_label_intent`, `client`, `pass_id`, `prev_snapshot`) and RETURN `(mutations, absent_alive_fields)` instead of the out-param.\n\n## Scope\nIn: comment-cluster extraction + the config-object/return-tuple refactor; preserve the idempotent diff contract exactly. Out: changing what mutations are computed.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] `outbound_comments.py` created (>100 LOC) holding the comment-diff cluster; `outbound_differ.py` imports it.\n- [ ] `outbound_differ.py` drops BELOW 800 LOC and is REMOVED from `.github/module-size-allowlist.txt`.\n- [ ] `compute_outbound_mutations` takes an `OutboundDiffConfig` (no more 9 positional params) and returns `(mutations, absent_alive_fields)` (no mutable out-param).\n- [ ] Reconciler diff tests pass byte-for-byte; no behavior change to outbound mutations.","id":"1242-d8af-6b69-4b6b","parent_id":"5ca8-5993-ca83-40f1","priority":1,"tags":["audit-2026-06-27","oss-remediation"],"ticket_type":"story","title":"Risk 2: split outbound_differ.py along the comment-diff seam"},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"CREATE","timestamp":1782605239659933001,"uuid":"50ce1abb-1e73-4f43-b4d7-7c9f7f50d8cf"}